title: Spider-Geddon #2
body:
Yep. I was completely right! Just like last time, each of the side stories are important and actually play a big roll in what’s going to happen. That makes me very happy and excited. A big reason I dislike so many of marvel’s big event is because all the tie-in issues completely stop ongoing storylines for a story that doesn’t even effect what’s going on in the main event. They’re just there to help boost sales and its stupid. But Spider-Verse (and now Geddon) didn’t do that though. All the side stuff explains what everyone is doing and how they’re helping in between or during the main stuff. So, you could just get the bare bones main stuff, but to get the full picture, you gotta read everything. And that makes the whole thing feel bigger and more important. 

But yeah. This issue was great! I love how they’re fighting each other and setting up their different plans to take down the Inheritors. I also really liked how Miles immediately brought up bringing back 616 Peter and Jessica, but then it was shot down because Otto is all kill happy. I can really understand both sides to that argument and it’ll be super interesting to see how it all plays out. I am excited!!

-Chuck
